Based on the forensic evidence in Source 111 (Contact Scrolled Up) and Source 112 (Contract Scrolled Down), you have established a distinct visual language: Obsidian, Glass, and Monospace Telemetry.
However, an Account is not a Person. A Person is a decision-maker; an Account is a Load Source. It is a physical asset sitting on the grid.
If you simply clone the Contact page, you fail. The Contact page answers "Who are they?" The Account page must answer "How do they consume?"
Here is the architectural blueprint for the Account Details Page, adapting your current style to fit Asset Intelligence.
1. The Header: "Corporate Entity"
Refers to Source 111 Header Style
• Visual: Identical layout to the Contact Header. Large Avatar on the left (Company Logo or First Initial), Name in Bold White, "Industry/Vertical" in Grey (replaces Job Title).
• Quick Actions (Top Right):
    ◦ Globe Icon: Link to Website.
    ◦ LinkedIn Icon: Link to Company LinkedIn.
    ◦ Map Icon (New): A "Pin" icon that opens the Infrastructure Map [Source 139] focused on this specific facility.
• Status Chip: [ STATUS: ACTIVE_LOAD ] (Green) or [ STATUS: PROSPECT ] (Amber).
2. The Three-Column Layout (The "Grid Topology")
We will retain your 3-column implied structure but repurpose the slots.
Column A: The Physics (Left Rail)
Refers to "Uplinks" and "Position Maturity" in Source 111
1. Primary Uplink (Contact Info):
    ◦ Main Office Phone (Click to Dial).
    ◦ Corporate Website domain.
2. Asset Recon (Location):
    ◦ Service Address: Display the physical address.
    ◦ Zone Identifier: A monospace tag reading LZ_NORTH or LZ_HOUSTON [Source 117]. This is critical for knowing their scarcity pricing exposure.
3. Volatility Profile (The Math):
    ◦ Replace "Strike Price" with "Load Factor".
        ▪ Visual: A 0-100% bar. If >60% (Good), color it Green. If <40% (Bad/Peaky), color it Red. This tells you immediately if they have a Demand Ratchet problem [Source 912].
    ◦ Annual Volume: "2.4 GWh" (Use Gigawatts for large accounts, it looks more expensive).
Column B: The Infrastructure (Center - The Wide Column)
Refers to "Forensic Log Stream" in Source 111
1. Forensic Brief (Firmographics):
    ◦ Keep the AI-generated summary section. It explains what the company does (e.g., "Manufacturing facility with 24/7 shifts...").
2. The "Meter Array" (The Missing Feature):
    ◦ Critique: An Account is often a parent entity with multiple meters (ESI IDs). You cannot just have one "Contract."
    ◦ Implementation: Below the summary, render a "Meter Array" Grid.
        ▪ Visual: Small glass cards for each ESI ID.
        ▪ Data: ESI: 1044... | Rate: $0.045 | Exp: Oct 2026.
3. Data Locker (Files):
    ◦ Place your "Data Ingestion" dropzone here. It must accept Bills, LOAs, and Contracts.
    ◦ Auto-Tagging: When a file is dropped, tag it with the specific Account ID.
Column C: The Network (Right Rail)
Refers to "Recent Calls" in Source 112
1. Stakeholder Map (New Feature):
    ◦ The Problem: You need to know who works here.
    ◦ The Fix: A list of linked Contacts.
    ◦ Visual: Small rows with Avatar + Name + Title. Click to jump to their Contact Page.
2. Engagement Stream (Digital Exhaust):
    ◦ Keep the "Digital Exhaust" component we designed previously (Emails, Clicks).
3. Transmission Log:
    ◦ Show calls associated with any contact at this account.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. Implementation Instructions (React/Next.js)
Here is how to structure the page to reuse your existing components while adding the Meter Array.
// AccountDetailsPage.tsx

export default function AccountDetailsPage({ account }) {
  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen bg-zinc-950 text-white p-6">
      
      {/* 1. HEADER (Reused from Contact Page) */}
      <EntityHeader 
        title={account.name}
        subtitle={account.industry}
        status={account.status}
        actions={[
          { icon: <Globe />, action: () => window.open(account.website) },
          { icon: <Linkedin />, action: () => window.open(account.linkedin) },
          { icon: <MapPin />, action: () => openMapModal(account.coordinates) } // NEW
        ]}
      />

      <div className="grid grid-cols-12 gap-6 mt-8">
        
        {/* 2. LEFT RAIL: PHYSICS & FIRMOGRAPHICS */}
        <div className="col-span-3 space-y-6">
          <UplinkCard phone={account.phone} website={account.website} />
          
          <div className="bg-zinc-900/50 border border-white/5 rounded-2xl p-4">
            <h3 className="text-xs font-mono text-zinc-500 mb-4">VOLATILITY_PROFILE</h3>
            <MetricRow label="LOAD_ZONE" value={account.zone} type="code" />
            <MetricRow label="ANNUAL_VOL" value={`${account.annualUsage} kWh`} />
            <LoadFactorBar value={account.loadFactor} /> {/* NEW: Visual Bar */}
          </div>
          
          <AddressCard address={account.billingAddress} />
        </div>

        {/* 3. CENTER: NARRATIVE & INFRASTRUCTURE */}
        <div className="col-span-6 space-y-6">
          {/* AI Summary */}
          <ForensicLogStream content={account.aiSummary} />
          
          {/* THE METER ARRAY (The "Missing" Feature) */}
          <div className="space-y-3">
            <div className="flex items-center justify-between">
              <h3 className="text-xs font-mono text-zinc-500 uppercase">Active Meters (ESI-IDs)</h3>
              <button className="text-[10px] text-[#002FA7] hover:underline">ADD METER +</button>
            </div>
            
            {account.meters.map(meter => (
              <div key={meter.id} className="flex items-center justify-between p-4 bg-zinc-900/30 border border-white/5 rounded-xl hover:border-white/10 transition-all">
                <div>
                  <div className="font-mono text-xs text-zinc-300">{meter.esiId}</div>
                  <div className="text-[10px] text-zinc-500">{meter.address}</div>
                </div>
                <div className="text-right">
                  <div className="text-sm font-medium text-white">{meter.contract.rate}¢</div>
                  <div className="text-[10px] text-emerald-500">Exp: {meter.contract.endDate}</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>

          {/* Data Locker */}
          <DataIngestionCard relatedId={account.id} type="account" />
        </div>

        {/* 4. RIGHT RAIL: NETWORK & ACTIVITY */}
        <div className="col-span-3 space-y-6">
          {/* Linked People */}
          <div className="bg-zinc-900/50 border border-white/5 rounded-2xl p-4">
             <h3 className="text-xs font-mono text-zinc-500 mb-4 uppercase">Stakeholders</h3>
             <div className="space-y-3">
               {account.contacts.map(contact => (
                 <ContactMiniCard key={contact.id} contact={contact} />
               ))}
             </div>
          </div>

          {/* Activity Feed */}
          <EngagementStream entityId={account.id} />
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
The "Steve Jobs" Difference
• Don't call it "Meters": Call the section "Grid Connection Points."
• Don't call it "Related Contacts": Call it "Command Chain" or "Stakeholders."
• The Load Factor Bar: This is the most important visual on the page. It instantly tells you if this client is efficient (easy to price) or inefficient (hard to price/high demand charges). If you don't have this data yet, show a "grayed out" bar with a button: [ CALCULATE FROM BILL ].